WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.559 --> 00:00:06.139
I wanna play in the NFL.

2
00:00:06.239 --> 00:00:09.780
I want a life better than
the one I've been living.

3
00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:12.580
You gotta save yourself.
cuz out here is every

4
00:00:12.680 --> 00:00:13.820
man for themselves.

5
00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:15.340
You need a family.

6
00:00:15.440 --> 00:00:17.681
I'm hoping you choose
to be a part of mine.

7
00:00:20.241 --> 00:00:22.481
'Cause I've already chosen you.

8
00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:30.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

9
00:00:34.803 --> 00:00:37.863
We were just trying
to tell a story

10
00:00:37.963 --> 00:00:41.103
that felt authentic about
black youth in America

11
00:00:41.203 --> 00:00:43.204
and the pursuit of a dream.

12
00:00:44.084 --> 00:00:45.344
I auditioned in London.

13
00:00:45.444 --> 00:00:48.344
I got the call from my
agent at like 10 p.m.

14
00:00:48.444 --> 00:00:51.005
and I had to be on a flight
to L.A. the next day.

15
00:00:52.565 --> 00:00:54.905
I thought I was
going to get fired

16
00:00:55.005 --> 00:00:57.785
for most of the pilot and
like half of season one.

17
00:00:57.885 --> 00:00:59.845
When I had the opportunity
to come to Los Angeles.

18
00:00:59.886 --> 00:01:01.746
my parents were. of
course. very weary

19
00:01:01.846 --> 00:01:03.382
and thought that maybe
this was a scam and I

20
00:01:03.406 --> 00:01:04.586
was gonna get kidnapped.

21
00:01:04.686 --> 00:01:06.827
Fortunately for me and
them. that didn't happen.

22
00:01:06.927 --> 00:01:09.227
I just knew it was good and
I knew that it was a job

23
00:01:09.327 --> 00:01:10.507
and that I needed one.

24
00:01:10.607 --> 00:01:12.787
So I was very grateful
to be working.

25
00:01:12.887 --> 00:01:16.708
I was in LA with my dad
on the Santa Monica Pier.

26
00:01:16.808 --> 00:01:19.708
It was like the most
surreal. magical moment

27
00:01:19.808 --> 00:01:23.308
to get that news in such an
iconic Los Angeles landmark.

28
00:01:23.408 --> 00:01:24.589
And then I met the cast.

29
00:01:24.689 --> 00:01:26.869
The cast was amazing
and talented

30
00:01:26.969 --> 00:01:28.989
and youthful and energetic.

31
00:01:29.089 --> 00:01:30.425
Everything about the
audition process

32
00:01:30.449 --> 00:01:32.190
just flowed and matched up.

33
00:01:32.290 --> 00:01:33.546
And the synchronicity was crazy.

34
00:01:33.570 --> 00:01:35.110
And so I kind of
knew that this was

35
00:01:35.210 --> 00:01:37.370
where I was gonna be for the
next few years of my life.

36
00:01:37.410 --> 00:01:41.391
I felt like it was the
precipice of something big.

37
00:01:41.491 --> 00:01:44.231
There was this like
palpable chemistry.

38
00:01:44.331 --> 00:01:46.831
You could feel that from
the very beginning.

39
00:01:46.931 --> 00:01:50.192
We've been blessed to have
a really fun. cohesive set.

40
00:01:50.292 --> 00:01:51.672
We gelled instantly.

41
00:01:51.772 --> 00:01:53.872
And the writing held
up. and I knew we had a

42
00:01:53.972 --> 00:01:55.352
gift on our hands.

43
00:01:55.452 --> 00:01:57.389
I was so excited to learn that
I was gonna be on the show.

44
00:01:57.413 --> 00:01:59.633
It was surreal. truly surreal.

45
00:01:59.733 --> 00:02:03.153
My life changed
from that point on.

46
00:02:03.253 --> 00:02:06.994
I'm obsessed with YA shows.
have been since I was a kid.

47
00:02:07.094 --> 00:02:09.194
still am as a grown adult.

48
00:02:09.294 --> 00:02:11.234
You know. I
remember when we met.

49
00:02:11.334 --> 00:02:12.514
First day of Little League.

50
00:02:12.614 --> 00:02:14.071
Man. I didn't even
know you was a girl.

51
00:02:14.095 --> 00:02:15.951
That's 'cause I striked
your ass out three times.

52
00:02:15.975 --> 00:02:17.995
Twice. man. you did
that twice. all right?

53
00:02:18.095 --> 00:02:19.791
Man. when I first got the
news that I got the role.

54
00:02:19.815 --> 00:02:21.315
I was so excited.

55
00:02:21.415 --> 00:02:22.655
I loved it. I loved being Coop.

56
00:02:22.736 --> 00:02:24.556
I loved bringing that to life.

57
00:02:24.656 --> 00:02:26.676
And just giving my
girl a platform

58
00:02:26.776 --> 00:02:28.316
and all the girls
that look like her.

59
00:02:28.416 --> 00:02:31.597
I don't want you hanging around
that Patience girl anymore.

60
00:02:31.697 --> 00:02:35.237
You think Patience's
trouble because she's gay?

61
00:02:35.337 --> 00:02:38.157
That would make me trouble.
since I'm gay. too.

62
00:02:38.257 --> 00:02:39.318
It was emotional.

63
00:02:39.418 --> 00:02:41.118
It was a little bit of drama.

64
00:02:41.218 --> 00:02:42.798
It turned out to be
a lot of everything.

65
00:02:42.898 --> 00:02:44.718
but the experience
was like none other.

66
00:02:44.818 --> 00:02:46.398
My very first day.
my first episode.

67
00:02:46.498 --> 00:02:48.679
we needed them to ad-lib
just a birthday song.

68
00:02:48.779 --> 00:02:50.195
You know. there was
nothing scripted.

69
00:02:50.219 --> 00:02:52.035
And so they were like. OK. well.
what do you want us to do?

70
00:02:52.059 --> 00:02:54.159
I said. put whatever's your
spin on happy birthday.

71
00:02:54.259 --> 00:02:54.880
Happy birthday.

72
00:02:54.980 --> 00:02:56.200
And it was phenomenal.

73
00:02:56.300 --> 00:03:00.920
♪ Happy birthday. happy
birthday. happy birth... ♪

74
00:03:01.020 --> 00:03:03.601
And in that moment. I'm like.
"Oh. okay. so this is easy."

75
00:03:03.701 --> 00:03:05.001
[ Laughs ]

76
00:03:05.101 --> 00:03:06.637
I'm like. "I just need to
give them just a little bit.

77
00:03:06.661 --> 00:03:08.357
and then they can take
it to another level."

78
00:03:08.381 --> 00:03:10.801
And that was literally my
first scene on the show.

79
00:03:10.901 --> 00:03:14.402
♪ Happy birthday. happy
birthday. happy birth... ♪

80
00:03:14.502 --> 00:03:17.922
I was just excited about
being able to take the genre

81
00:03:18.022 --> 00:03:21.803
but also honestly reflect what
my sons were going through.

82
00:03:21.903 --> 00:03:24.123
Everybody's gone to junior
high and high school.

83
00:03:24.223 --> 00:03:26.123
We've all dealt with bullies.

84
00:03:26.223 --> 00:03:27.803
She mean more like you.

85
00:03:27.903 --> 00:03:29.644
Having problems with class.

86
00:03:29.744 --> 00:03:30.644
What does that look like?

87
00:03:30.744 --> 00:03:32.564
I had a 10th of
your talent. bro.

88
00:03:32.664 --> 00:03:35.584
I say we get this
place and bounce.

89
00:03:40.305 --> 00:03:43.605
There's something in these
episodes and these seasons

90
00:03:43.705 --> 00:03:46.166
that people really connect with.

91
00:03:46.266 --> 00:03:50.806
It's taking life situations
and giving you options.

92
00:03:50.906 --> 00:03:53.407
Spencer James.

93
00:03:53.507 --> 00:03:55.007
Billy Baker.

94
00:03:55.107 --> 00:03:56.807
Varsity coach. Beverly High.

95
00:03:56.907 --> 00:04:00.567
As a young actor. you watch
other actors do scenes.

96
00:04:00.667 --> 00:04:03.768
and you can't wait for your
turn to say those lines.

97
00:04:03.868 --> 00:04:05.368
I need you to come play for me.

98
00:04:05.468 --> 00:04:06.564
That was one of those lines.

99
00:04:06.588 --> 00:04:09.528
And it was dark and lit.

100
00:04:09.628 --> 00:04:10.628
It was cool.

101
00:04:10.669 --> 00:04:12.689
I can get your way out. man.

102
00:04:12.789 --> 00:04:14.649
I was a kid that
grew up watching TV.

103
00:04:14.749 --> 00:04:17.369
I used to always
entertain my family.

104
00:04:17.469 --> 00:04:19.890
telling jokes or
imitating somebody.

105
00:04:19.990 --> 00:04:22.090
I was just like. yeah.
I want to be on TV.

106
00:04:22.190 --> 00:04:23.410
I want to be an actor.

107
00:04:23.510 --> 00:04:24.810
Meet Preach.

108
00:04:24.910 --> 00:04:25.970
He just got out.

109
00:04:26.070 --> 00:04:27.291
What up. Preach?

110
00:04:27.391 --> 00:04:29.651
Something exciting about
being able to step

111
00:04:29.751 --> 00:04:31.771
into somebody else's
shoes and try to see

112
00:04:31.871 --> 00:04:33.131
the world from their lens.

113
00:04:33.231 --> 00:04:34.151
What's up with you
and this kid. Dad?

114
00:04:34.231 --> 00:04:35.252
Why do you care so much?

115
00:04:35.352 --> 00:04:37.612
I come from Spencer's
neighborhood.

116
00:04:37.712 --> 00:04:39.572
You have no idea
what that's like.

117
00:04:39.672 --> 00:04:42.813
His understanding of
which box do I check.

118
00:04:42.913 --> 00:04:44.013
Guess I don't. yeah.

119
00:04:44.113 --> 00:04:45.653
Jordan definitely
struggled with that.

120
00:04:45.753 --> 00:04:48.653
And I kind of struggled
with that as a young man.

121
00:04:48.753 --> 00:04:51.374
I was adopted and
not understanding

122
00:04:51.474 --> 00:04:53.374
where I was coming
from to some degree.

123
00:04:53.474 --> 00:04:56.294
But being able to play Jordan
has made me understand that no

124
00:04:56.394 --> 00:04:59.655
matter where you're from.
you are who you are.

125
00:04:59.755 --> 00:05:02.935
You sure about this.
living in Beverly Hills?

126
00:05:03.035 --> 00:05:08.216
Look. Ma. if you don't
want this. I won't go.

127
00:05:08.316 --> 00:05:11.776
OK. just say the word.
and I'll call them.

128
00:05:11.876 --> 00:05:15.656
No. I ask you to give yourself
a chance at something more.

129
00:05:15.756 --> 00:05:17.757
This is what's best
for you. Spencer.

130
00:05:25.398 --> 00:05:27.778
Welcome to Beverly Hills.

131
00:05:27.878 --> 00:05:29.858
Being born and raised in
Inglewood. California.

132
00:05:29.958 --> 00:05:33.499
Los Angeles native. this show
I connected with immediately

133
00:05:33.599 --> 00:05:36.019
because I went to a
predominantly white school

134
00:05:36.119 --> 00:05:38.299
and then transferred
to Dorsey High School.

135
00:05:38.399 --> 00:05:39.415
which is in the inner city.

136
00:05:39.439 --> 00:05:40.659
Crips or Bloods?

137
00:05:40.759 --> 00:05:41.820
Excuse me?

138
00:05:41.920 --> 00:05:43.496
Yo. yo. he's just
joking. man. ignore him.

139
00:05:43.520 --> 00:05:45.860
Nah. that ain't sound
like a joke to me. bro.

140
00:05:45.960 --> 00:05:47.100
Don't be so sensitive.

141
00:05:47.200 --> 00:05:48.540
Sensitive.

142
00:05:48.640 --> 00:05:52.261
These are stories that I've
actually witnessed firsthand.

143
00:05:52.361 --> 00:05:53.981
The hell are you doing?

144
00:05:54.081 --> 00:05:56.661
I'm picking you up in your
red car. in your red hat.

145
00:05:56.761 --> 00:05:58.422
Don't get your head blown off.

146
00:05:58.522 --> 00:06:01.262
I'm just playing.

147
00:06:01.362 --> 00:06:03.342
I'm just playing.

148
00:06:03.442 --> 00:06:05.442
Just drive. bro.

149
00:06:07.683 --> 00:06:09.303
Hey.

150
00:06:09.403 --> 00:06:10.263
Come here often?

151
00:06:10.363 --> 00:06:12.063
Seeing this?

152
00:06:12.163 --> 00:06:13.263
We need to get rid of him.

153
00:06:13.363 --> 00:06:15.624
It felt like it was
going to be high school

154
00:06:15.724 --> 00:06:16.984
all over again.

155
00:06:17.084 --> 00:06:18.104
It's okay.

156
00:06:18.204 --> 00:06:19.084
If you don't have a
computer. just pair up

157
00:06:19.164 --> 00:06:21.164
with a classmate for now.

158
00:06:24.885 --> 00:06:26.905
You can share with me.

159
00:06:27.005 --> 00:06:30.025
Growing alongside Olivia.
I was able to bring a

160
00:06:30.125 --> 00:06:31.666
lot of myself into her.

161
00:06:31.766 --> 00:06:35.306
I was so terrified of losing the
people I love over a mistake

162
00:06:35.406 --> 00:06:36.986
I can barely even remember.

163
00:06:37.086 --> 00:06:39.787
I've just been so grateful that
so many people have been able

164
00:06:39.887 --> 00:06:41.887
to resonate with her
character. and that means that

165
00:06:41.967 --> 00:06:44.267
I did my job well and that
made it all worthwhile.

166
00:06:44.367 --> 00:06:45.387
So. show Friday?

167
00:06:45.487 --> 00:06:47.488
To date?

168
00:06:49.368 --> 00:06:50.628
To date?

169
00:06:50.728 --> 00:06:51.908
(upbeat music)

170
00:06:52.008 --> 00:06:53.348
Oh. Spence!

171
00:06:53.448 --> 00:06:54.308
What's good. man?

172
00:06:54.408 --> 00:06:55.028
Hey. what up. bro?

173
00:06:55.128 --> 00:06:55.949
How you feeling?

174
00:06:56.049 --> 00:06:56.669
Okay. you hear me?

175
00:06:56.769 --> 00:06:58.069
For me. I play sports.

176
00:06:58.169 --> 00:06:58.909
That's my connection.

177
00:06:59.009 --> 00:07:00.189
I play football.

178
00:07:00.289 --> 00:07:02.589
I understand where these
players are coming from.

179
00:07:02.689 --> 00:07:04.750
dealing with the pressures.
especially if you're

180
00:07:04.850 --> 00:07:06.670
a star athlete.

181
00:07:06.770 --> 00:07:09.030
The pressures from
home. the pressures at

182
00:07:09.130 --> 00:07:09.990
school to perform.

183
00:07:10.090 --> 00:07:10.950
(laughing)

184
00:07:11.050 --> 00:07:11.530
All right. good work. son.

185
00:07:11.610 --> 00:07:11.850
Thanks. y'all.

186
00:07:11.930 --> 00:07:12.951
Woo!

187
00:07:13.051 --> 00:07:14.271
That's good stuff.

188
00:07:14.371 --> 00:07:15.951
That's how you play football.

189
00:07:16.051 --> 00:07:18.091
Better get comfortable there.

190
00:07:22.892 --> 00:07:25.552
(typing)

191
00:07:25.652 --> 00:07:28.432
The writers always either
have me screaming or crying.

192
00:07:28.532 --> 00:07:30.533
so that's like
process number one.

193
00:07:33.533 --> 00:07:36.073
We are very particular
with every single look.

194
00:07:36.173 --> 00:07:39.634
Are they underprivileged.
or is it super preppy?

195
00:07:39.734 --> 00:07:44.074
Does it look like money. or does
it look like hand-me-downs?

196
00:07:44.174 --> 00:07:49.235
I try to sprinkle in pieces
that smaller companies design.

197
00:07:49.335 --> 00:07:53.195
companies that don't get the
light shined on them too often.

198
00:07:53.295 --> 00:07:54.356
I try.

199
00:07:54.456 --> 00:07:56.316
[ Laughs ]

200
00:07:56.416 --> 00:07:58.076
I wanted to make
sure that the music

201
00:07:58.176 --> 00:08:00.516
was really authentic
to the series.

202
00:08:00.616 --> 00:08:03.637
And to do that. that
meant really recognizing

203
00:08:03.737 --> 00:08:06.197
where we were. that we
were in Los Angeles.

204
00:08:06.297 --> 00:08:09.237
that we were in South
Central or in Crenshaw.

205
00:08:09.337 --> 00:08:12.758
I insisted that whatever we put
in that first pilot episode.

206
00:08:12.858 --> 00:08:14.998
there was going to be
a Nipsey Hussle song.

207
00:08:15.098 --> 00:08:15.798
(RAPPING) Once slice.

208
00:08:15.898 --> 00:08:17.118
Got to roll the dice.

209
00:08:17.218 --> 00:08:19.959
That's why all my life. I
be grinding all my life.

210
00:08:20.059 --> 00:08:22.719
What Spencer did was come
from a neighborhood.

211
00:08:22.819 --> 00:08:24.399
work hard to fulfill
your dreams.

212
00:08:24.499 --> 00:08:25.759
but then also give back.

213
00:08:25.859 --> 00:08:28.120
That's exactly who
Nipsey Hussle was.

214
00:08:28.220 --> 00:08:30.440
So to me. there wasn't
a better place to start

215
00:08:30.540 --> 00:08:32.540
than right there.

216
00:08:38.501 --> 00:08:41.081
The most fun I've ever had
was probably any football

217
00:08:41.181 --> 00:08:42.181
scene that we ever shot.

218
00:08:42.261 --> 00:08:45.522
Please welcome your
Beverly High Eagles.

219
00:08:45.622 --> 00:08:46.242
(cheering)

220
00:08:46.342 --> 00:08:49.042
♪ Back to my ways ♪

221
00:08:49.142 --> 00:08:51.882
We had background players
who played college football.

222
00:08:51.982 --> 00:08:54.923
who played in the NFL.

223
00:08:55.023 --> 00:08:56.283
And they are massive.

224
00:08:56.383 --> 00:08:59.443
When you get next to them.
these dudes are huge.

225
00:08:59.543 --> 00:09:02.084
What a block by Spencer James!

226
00:09:02.184 --> 00:09:04.604
They hold practices.
they put like a package

227
00:09:04.704 --> 00:09:05.964
of plays together.

228
00:09:06.064 --> 00:09:08.685
They base that off of
whatever we write in script.

229
00:09:08.785 --> 00:09:10.201
If we're like. okay.
this is a full game.

230
00:09:10.225 --> 00:09:11.605
we might need like 10 plays.

231
00:09:11.705 --> 00:09:14.245
They'll organize the 10 plays.
they will practice those plays.

232
00:09:14.345 --> 00:09:16.845
they will be beautifully
orchestrated when the day comes.

233
00:09:16.945 --> 00:09:20.246
And then they have doubles
for all of our actors.

234
00:09:20.346 --> 00:09:22.166
And shout out to Mike
Bailey in particular.

235
00:09:22.266 --> 00:09:23.466
because that dude is a baller.

236
00:09:23.506 --> 00:09:25.647
I mean. he can really
heave that thing 60 yards.

237
00:09:25.747 --> 00:09:26.887
He is legit.

238
00:09:26.987 --> 00:09:29.207
And then the evolution
and growth of Daniel

239
00:09:29.307 --> 00:09:31.847
has been great in terms
of a dude who had never

240
00:09:31.947 --> 00:09:34.968
played football before to a
guy who worked his ass off

241
00:09:35.068 --> 00:09:37.068
and got there.

242
00:09:39.308 --> 00:09:41.408
[GRUNTING]

243
00:09:41.508 --> 00:09:43.289
We all got to watch the
pilot together. too.

244
00:09:43.389 --> 00:09:46.809
when we were on
set. and it just...

245
00:09:46.909 --> 00:09:48.089
it was lightning in a bottle.

246
00:09:48.189 --> 00:09:49.509
Welcome to Beverly
Hills. Spencer.

247
00:09:49.549 --> 00:09:52.330
I don't think I had any idea
of what it would become

248
00:09:52.430 --> 00:09:53.730
or what it would mean to people.

249
00:09:53.830 --> 00:09:56.570
I told my reps between
season one and season two.

250
00:09:56.670 --> 00:09:58.691
I don't want to go
off any other jobs.

251
00:09:58.791 --> 00:10:00.127
because I feel like this
show is coming back.

252
00:10:00.151 --> 00:10:01.447
I'll be damned if I
let you back down.

253
00:10:01.471 --> 00:10:03.651
It was a bold move on my part.

254
00:10:03.751 --> 00:10:05.571
That's just me
betting on the show.

255
00:10:05.671 --> 00:10:08.212
I was like. OK. this is serious.

256
00:10:08.312 --> 00:10:11.292
I just felt really excited
that I got to do a show

257
00:10:11.392 --> 00:10:13.332
that I would have watched.

258
00:10:13.432 --> 00:10:17.793
But beyond that. I had like
really no idea what was to come.

259
00:10:26.034 --> 00:10:28.734
When I first discovered
All American. it felt

260
00:10:28.834 --> 00:10:30.054
so familiar to me.

261
00:10:30.154 --> 00:10:32.455
It made me lean more into
my authenticity because

262
00:10:32.555 --> 00:10:35.255
people connect with what's
real and not what's perfect.

263
00:10:35.355 --> 00:10:37.355
That never be the
same around here.

264
00:10:40.476 --> 00:10:44.176
Coming back for season two.
way more people knew who we were

265
00:10:44.276 --> 00:10:45.736
and just the energy had shifted.

266
00:10:45.836 --> 00:10:47.576
That's just a taste
of your new reality.

267
00:10:47.676 --> 00:10:50.337
I had people who
I really admired

268
00:10:50.437 --> 00:10:52.897
start to come up to me and
say. "I'm a really big

269
00:10:52.997 --> 00:10:53.997
fan of the show."

270
00:10:54.077 --> 00:10:56.257
It was really cool
being called coach

271
00:10:56.357 --> 00:10:57.978
outside of the set.

272
00:10:58.078 --> 00:11:01.138
Yeah. - I will
never forget Daniel

273
00:11:01.238 --> 00:11:04.018
taking Breezy by the hand
and bringing her up to

274
00:11:04.118 --> 00:11:06.099
me on set and going.
"Hey. Madonna. did you

275
00:11:06.199 --> 00:11:07.379
know that Breezy can rap?"

276
00:11:07.479 --> 00:11:09.739
And I went. "No."

277
00:11:09.839 --> 00:11:12.979
And lo and behold. it
became "You Don't Ask."

278
00:11:13.079 --> 00:11:18.700
♪ You don't ask So
I don't say none ♪

279
00:11:18.800 --> 00:11:23.541
Which I think is an incredible
anthem for the LGBTQ+ community.

280
00:11:23.641 --> 00:11:26.541
I mean. it's a huge theme
about whether your parents

281
00:11:26.641 --> 00:11:29.781
are willing to talk to you
about who you really are.

282
00:11:29.881 --> 00:11:32.062
The core of this show is
about people building

283
00:11:32.162 --> 00:11:33.702
dreams and achieving them.

284
00:11:33.802 --> 00:11:37.342
So why wouldn't I want to give
an unknown artist or give

285
00:11:37.442 --> 00:11:40.063
someone starting out exposure?

286
00:11:40.163 --> 00:11:43.523
And we've had people go on to
become Grammy-nominated artists.

287
00:11:47.124 --> 00:11:50.104
After the fires in Los Angeles.
I was paying special attention

288
00:11:50.204 --> 00:11:51.744
to artists who lost their homes.

289
00:11:51.844 --> 00:11:53.584
And I got an artist
who lost her home.

290
00:11:53.684 --> 00:11:56.345
I got one of her
songs in an episode.

291
00:11:56.445 --> 00:11:57.445
There's a bigger picture.

292
00:11:57.525 --> 00:11:59.745
It's people. it's
lives. it's dreams.

293
00:11:59.845 --> 00:12:01.945
That's better than any paycheck.

294
00:12:02.045 --> 00:12:04.786
Secretly. I snuck in a
couple parental lessons.

295
00:12:04.886 --> 00:12:07.266
If there was something I
wanted my son to hear.

296
00:12:07.366 --> 00:12:09.106
occasionally I'd put
it in Grace's mouth.

297
00:12:09.206 --> 00:12:11.707
Most of us don't even start
the race until it's over.

298
00:12:11.807 --> 00:12:13.827
You've been given a
chance to start on time.

299
00:12:13.927 --> 00:12:14.983
He'd be like. "Mom. it's crazy.

300
00:12:15.007 --> 00:12:16.023
Do you know what Grace
said to Spencer?"

301
00:12:16.047 --> 00:12:17.947
And I'd be like. "Oh.
what'd she say?"

302
00:12:18.047 --> 00:12:20.388
Go win that race
for the rest of us.

303
00:12:20.488 --> 00:12:22.708
It's what you do with your
success that matters.

304
00:12:22.808 --> 00:12:25.468
I had kids sending me
messages through social media

305
00:12:25.568 --> 00:12:27.788
asking me like real
life questions.

306
00:12:27.888 --> 00:12:29.305
It really kind of
reflected back to me

307
00:12:29.329 --> 00:12:32.629
how serious kids were
looking up to Grace James.

308
00:12:32.729 --> 00:12:36.390
I would get these
paragraphs from fans.

309
00:12:36.490 --> 00:12:38.870
like. "Oh my gosh. my son
and I haven't discussed

310
00:12:38.970 --> 00:12:41.310
the loss of his father until
we watched the episode

311
00:12:41.410 --> 00:12:42.950
where Spencer lost Corey."

312
00:12:43.050 --> 00:12:46.711
(sobbing)

313
00:12:46.811 --> 00:12:49.711
(screaming)

314
00:12:49.811 --> 00:12:52.791
I lost my dad when
I was in my 20s.

315
00:12:52.891 --> 00:12:55.152
and I'm still processing
20-something years later.

316
00:12:55.252 --> 00:12:57.032
and so to hear that
something we did

317
00:12:57.132 --> 00:13:00.952
was helping families
heal was incredible.

318
00:13:01.052 --> 00:13:03.029
I was like. "Oh. we might
actually be doing something

319
00:13:03.053 --> 00:13:05.353
that's connecting people
in a way deeper way

320
00:13:05.453 --> 00:13:07.353
than we even realized."

321
00:13:07.453 --> 00:13:09.594
It's a culture shifter.

322
00:13:09.694 --> 00:13:12.594
Mothers have told us this
show is appointment TV

323
00:13:12.694 --> 00:13:14.994
for a mom and her son or
for a dad and his daughter.

324
00:13:15.094 --> 00:13:18.275
I've had a ton of single
fathers come up to me and say.

325
00:13:18.375 --> 00:13:21.035
"Man. I love that relationship
between your daughter.

326
00:13:21.135 --> 00:13:22.315
I'm a girl dad."

327
00:13:22.415 --> 00:13:24.035
And they totally relate to it.

328
00:13:24.135 --> 00:13:26.156
You about to teach me
another lesson. huh?

329
00:13:26.256 --> 00:13:29.756
We don't see too many Black
fathers on television

330
00:13:29.856 --> 00:13:32.916
as far as fighting for
custody of their kids.

331
00:13:33.016 --> 00:13:34.833
They're gonna take her away.
and I can't let that happen.

332
00:13:34.857 --> 00:13:36.557
And I think that's
something beautiful

333
00:13:36.657 --> 00:13:38.117
that this show tackled.

334
00:13:38.217 --> 00:13:41.797
The messages hit
major points in life.

335
00:13:41.897 --> 00:13:44.838
in sports. in parenting.
and in friendship.

336
00:13:44.938 --> 00:13:47.438
I thought I was talking
to my best friend.

337
00:13:47.538 --> 00:13:49.558
not a treacherous bitch.

338
00:13:49.658 --> 00:13:51.719
It's hard. but at
the end of the day.

339
00:13:51.819 --> 00:13:54.199
like if someone is your
friend. I think there should

340
00:13:54.299 --> 00:13:56.359
be an effort there to
make repair and show

341
00:13:56.459 --> 00:13:57.719
grace to the other person.

342
00:13:57.819 --> 00:13:59.840
Maybe now you can finally admit

343
00:13:59.940 --> 00:14:02.680
that you're a messy human who
screws up like the rest of us.

344
00:14:02.780 --> 00:14:04.480
And if the friendship
means a lot to you.

345
00:14:04.580 --> 00:14:06.156
I think you will find your
way back to each other.

346
00:14:06.180 --> 00:14:07.757
I really don't wanna
lose my best friend.

347
00:14:07.781 --> 00:14:09.641
There was a scene
that I had written

348
00:14:09.741 --> 00:14:11.321
in like season three.
Preach had this

349
00:14:11.421 --> 00:14:12.721
conversation with Spencer.

350
00:14:12.821 --> 00:14:14.517
I don't know why you and
Cooper still beefing.

351
00:14:14.541 --> 00:14:17.042
and honestly. I don't care.
but I know this much.

352
00:14:17.142 --> 00:14:19.642
He basically broke down.
like. if you're lucky.

353
00:14:19.742 --> 00:14:22.002
you might get three true
friends your entire life.

354
00:14:22.102 --> 00:14:24.042
I'm talking about sandbox.

355
00:14:24.142 --> 00:14:26.003
Day ones. ride or dies.

356
00:14:26.103 --> 00:14:28.563
Do everything possible to
keep them in your circle.

357
00:14:28.663 --> 00:14:30.603
There was a fan who
was gonna use that

358
00:14:30.703 --> 00:14:32.243
in this speech that
she was delivering

359
00:14:32.343 --> 00:14:34.084
for her school graduation.

360
00:14:34.184 --> 00:14:36.504
You never know when she kind
of releases it into the world.

361
00:14:36.544 --> 00:14:37.544
the impact it would have.

362
00:14:37.584 --> 00:14:38.484
♪ You're looking for love ♪

363
00:14:38.584 --> 00:14:40.244
We had teachers reach out to us

364
00:14:40.344 --> 00:14:41.881
to tell us they started
incorporating it

365
00:14:41.905 --> 00:14:43.925
into their classroom.
and it changed how they

366
00:14:44.025 --> 00:14:45.721
related to their students.
and it changed how

367
00:14:45.745 --> 00:14:47.845
their students were
showing up to class.

368
00:14:47.945 --> 00:14:50.566
That was beyond anything
we could have imagined.

369
00:14:50.666 --> 00:14:56.246
We focused on issues that people

370
00:14:56.346 --> 00:14:58.347
in our generation deal with.

371
00:15:00.227 --> 00:15:03.047
It's meant to be seen by
whoever it's meant to reach.

372
00:15:03.147 --> 00:15:05.007
♪ Reach out. reach out.
reach out. reach out ♪

373
00:15:05.107 --> 00:15:09.048
My favorite fan moment.
I had a guy approach me

374
00:15:09.148 --> 00:15:13.728
on the beach who told me that
Coop allowed him to come out.

375
00:15:13.828 --> 00:15:15.929
The 60-year-old
white man inspired

376
00:15:16.029 --> 00:15:18.029
by a young black teenage girl.

377
00:15:22.710 --> 00:15:25.610
And there was other things
like the opioid epidemic

378
00:15:25.710 --> 00:15:27.730
and depression.

379
00:15:27.830 --> 00:15:30.771
Addiction is a
very real disease.

380
00:15:30.871 --> 00:15:33.451
and when it takes over. it's
a very scary place to be in.

381
00:15:33.551 --> 00:15:36.091
I found some pills in my room.

382
00:15:36.191 --> 00:15:36.931
What?

383
00:15:37.031 --> 00:15:38.931
I was tempted. but it's fine.

384
00:15:39.031 --> 00:15:41.252
I threw them away and met
with my sponsor. so...

385
00:15:41.352 --> 00:15:42.152
Can we talk about
something else?

386
00:15:42.232 --> 00:15:42.652
No.

387
00:15:42.752 --> 00:15:43.752
Please?

388
00:15:43.832 --> 00:15:45.412
Please? - It was a
flashback moment

389
00:15:45.512 --> 00:15:49.133
where Olivia
overdoses. and. uh...

390
00:15:49.233 --> 00:15:51.973
Jordan finds her on the
couch. and then. you know.

391
00:15:52.073 --> 00:15:53.969
brings her to the foyer.
and next thing you know.

392
00:15:53.993 --> 00:15:55.770
Billy and Laura come in and
they try to revive her.

393
00:15:55.794 --> 00:15:56.974
Sorry. Mom. Dad.

394
00:15:57.074 --> 00:15:58.414
What's going on?

395
00:15:58.514 --> 00:16:01.934
I mean. that was really heavy
and so difficult to film.

396
00:16:02.034 --> 00:16:04.975
and I just remember feeling like
a weight of responsibility.

397
00:16:05.075 --> 00:16:07.255
like I really just. I
want to get this right.

398
00:16:07.355 --> 00:16:10.335
I can remember the
director on like the wide.

399
00:16:10.435 --> 00:16:12.812
The wide was like. "Hey. so you
know. you can save it." right?

400
00:16:12.836 --> 00:16:15.236
But I was just
uncontrollably sobbing.

401
00:16:16.756 --> 00:16:19.096
That was quite a
scene. quite a day.

402
00:16:19.196 --> 00:16:21.396
and I can just remember really
feeling heavy after that.

403
00:16:21.477 --> 00:16:24.177
But there is hope and always
a chance to get better.

404
00:16:24.277 --> 00:16:25.377
You did it.

405
00:16:25.477 --> 00:16:26.397
I just remember filming
the scene where

406
00:16:26.477 --> 00:16:28.257
she got her one
year of sobriety.

407
00:16:28.357 --> 00:16:30.978
That was a really.
really beautiful moment.

408
00:16:31.078 --> 00:16:33.738
I'm really proud to
have played Olivia.

409
00:16:33.838 --> 00:16:37.419
And I'm proud of myself. too.

410
00:16:37.519 --> 00:16:40.459
There have definitely been
times where this show

411
00:16:40.559 --> 00:16:43.459
is art imitating life.

412
00:16:43.559 --> 00:16:46.460
It's helped me personally.
like. work through and heal

413
00:16:46.560 --> 00:16:47.420
through things.

414
00:16:47.520 --> 00:16:49.220
Your mom. she suffered from

415
00:16:49.320 --> 00:16:52.500
depression. Depression can
be hereditary. sweetie.

416
00:16:52.600 --> 00:16:54.341
I think the biggest lesson that

417
00:16:54.441 --> 00:16:57.741
Layla has taught me is to
prioritize my mental health.

418
00:16:57.841 --> 00:17:00.621
I'm gonna need help
to get through this.

419
00:17:00.721 --> 00:17:02.982
And not feel the
stigma or shame that

420
00:17:03.082 --> 00:17:05.502
I think a lot of
people do still feel.

421
00:17:05.602 --> 00:17:07.702
Layla Keating.
checking myself in.

422
00:17:07.802 --> 00:17:09.522
So that was a beautiful
lesson she taught me

423
00:17:09.562 --> 00:17:13.303
and continues to teach me.

424
00:17:13.403 --> 00:17:16.183
(clapping)

425
00:17:16.283 --> 00:17:17.783
Hey. who's ready
to play football?

426
00:17:17.883 --> 00:17:19.504
It's TV. of course
we want the drama

427
00:17:19.604 --> 00:17:21.624
and we want all the things.

428
00:17:21.724 --> 00:17:25.104
But if we can also
show how relationships

429
00:17:25.204 --> 00:17:27.345
and friendships heal.
how families can heal.

430
00:17:27.445 --> 00:17:28.945
how families can
come back together.

431
00:17:29.045 --> 00:17:31.385
You know. Billy and
Laura. the affair.

432
00:17:31.485 --> 00:17:32.765
separating. coming
back together.

433
00:17:32.845 --> 00:17:35.586
(heavy breathing)

434
00:17:35.686 --> 00:17:38.586
If we can show even
a slice of that.

435
00:17:38.686 --> 00:17:40.826
maybe we're helping the
world sort of realize

436
00:17:40.926 --> 00:17:43.126
that it's okay to say. "I
messed up. I'm sorry."

437
00:17:44.447 --> 00:17:46.067
I always say I wanna
create content

438
00:17:46.167 --> 00:17:48.707
that leaves the world a better
place than how I found it.

439
00:17:48.807 --> 00:17:51.707
And when we realized on
kind of a mass scale

440
00:17:51.807 --> 00:17:53.447
how much that was
happening. we were like.

441
00:17:53.528 --> 00:17:54.708
"This is crazy."

442
00:17:54.808 --> 00:17:56.304
And then it's like. "We
have to keep going."

443
00:17:56.328 --> 00:18:00.008
The numbers really started to
pop at the end of season two.

444
00:18:01.409 --> 00:18:02.785
And then everybody
got locked inside.

445
00:18:02.809 --> 00:18:04.989
The man was being
treated for COVID-19.

446
00:18:05.089 --> 00:18:07.089
And that's when things
really took a turn.

447
00:18:14.930 --> 00:18:18.511
When I found All-American.
it was during the pandemic.

448
00:18:18.611 --> 00:18:22.671
I was in high school. and
people were very scared.

449
00:18:22.771 --> 00:18:27.192
You never forget a show that
brings oneness and hope

450
00:18:27.292 --> 00:18:28.512
in a time that feels hopeless.

451
00:18:28.612 --> 00:18:31.852
♪ All American ♪

452
00:18:32.252 --> 00:18:33.252
COVID was tough. man.

453
00:18:33.292 --> 00:18:34.313
Screening operation.

454
00:18:34.413 --> 00:18:36.053
Going through all
the testing protocols.

455
00:18:36.133 --> 00:18:38.113
We had to go through
zoning protocols.

456
00:18:38.213 --> 00:18:40.349
Actors gotta be in their zone.
crew have to be in their zone.

457
00:18:40.373 --> 00:18:42.274
If we ever had an actor
who tested positive.

458
00:18:42.374 --> 00:18:43.834
we would have to pivot.

459
00:18:43.934 --> 00:18:45.910
And sometimes we'd have to pull
actors who were available.

460
00:18:45.934 --> 00:18:48.154
We'd have to pull scenes
from future episodes.

461
00:18:48.254 --> 00:18:50.150
We'd have to bring in that
director from that episode

462
00:18:50.174 --> 00:18:51.871
and you had to kind of work
through all of that stuff.

463
00:18:51.895 --> 00:18:53.835
We only had like
maybe one shutdown.

464
00:18:53.935 --> 00:18:56.235
but we were always hit
with different actors

465
00:18:56.335 --> 00:18:57.335
who would get it.

466
00:18:57.415 --> 00:18:58.952
It was one of the most
challenging times.

467
00:18:58.976 --> 00:19:00.636
but I think one of
the greatest rewards

468
00:19:00.736 --> 00:19:03.836
is that every step of the
way. we always found a pivot.

469
00:19:03.936 --> 00:19:06.116
And at the end of
the day. it worked.

470
00:19:06.216 --> 00:19:07.917
COVID changed the
way we did things.

471
00:19:08.017 --> 00:19:10.037
but we had to just
get right in gear

472
00:19:10.137 --> 00:19:12.517
to talk about what was real.

473
00:19:12.617 --> 00:19:13.717
The heart of downtown LA.

474
00:19:13.817 --> 00:19:15.194
Everyone was like.
"Oh. is there gonna be a.

475
00:19:15.218 --> 00:19:16.338
Black Lives Matter episode?"

476
00:19:16.418 --> 00:19:18.718
I'm like. "Our entire
series is taking a stand

477
00:19:18.818 --> 00:19:21.318
on Black Lives Matter.
Black Joy Matters.

478
00:19:21.418 --> 00:19:24.359
Black Dreams Matter. Black Kids.
no matter what neighborhood

479
00:19:24.459 --> 00:19:25.559
you come from. matter."

480
00:19:25.659 --> 00:19:27.959
The way in which we
talked about that issue.

481
00:19:28.059 --> 00:19:29.835
Jordan being a biracial
kid from Beverly Hills

482
00:19:29.859 --> 00:19:32.320
and not really knowing how to
interact with police officers.

483
00:19:32.420 --> 00:19:34.040
We've done nothing wrong. man.

484
00:19:34.140 --> 00:19:36.400
Jordan. this is harassment.

485
00:19:36.500 --> 00:19:40.001
That. to me. was a scene
that we did so well.

486
00:19:40.101 --> 00:19:42.201
We did it in a way that
didn't feel like it was

487
00:19:42.301 --> 00:19:44.121
being shoved down your
throat as a viewer.

488
00:19:44.221 --> 00:19:45.681
Just keep looking
at me. all right?

489
00:19:45.781 --> 00:19:46.681
Just keep looking at me.

490
00:19:46.781 --> 00:19:49.082
We did our best
to not be preachy

491
00:19:49.182 --> 00:19:51.882
and not tell people what
to think and what to feel.

492
00:19:51.982 --> 00:19:54.802
but we also wanted
to shine light

493
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:57.603
on the very real experiences
that a lot of kids in America

494
00:19:57.703 --> 00:19:59.483
were going through at the time.

495
00:19:59.583 --> 00:20:02.443
If even one person looks at
those situations differently

496
00:20:02.543 --> 00:20:05.184
and now interacts with
Black youth differently.

497
00:20:06.544 --> 00:20:08.124
then that's why we do it.

498
00:20:08.224 --> 00:20:10.884
Tamika was a 21-year-old
girl from South LA.

499
00:20:10.984 --> 00:20:12.924
I've been really shy
in my whole life.

500
00:20:13.024 --> 00:20:14.965
When Liv had her podcast.
"Liv the Truth."

501
00:20:15.065 --> 00:20:17.365
she taught me how
to use my voice.

502
00:20:17.465 --> 00:20:20.645
There has to be a better
way to serve and protect.

503
00:20:20.745 --> 00:20:22.326
That was very healing.
just during those

504
00:20:22.426 --> 00:20:23.886
really difficult times.

505
00:20:23.986 --> 00:20:27.326
I would have gone crazy if I
didn't have an outlet for that.

506
00:20:27.426 --> 00:20:30.007
Writers' rooms are
super cathartic.

507
00:20:30.107 --> 00:20:31.887
We're pulling from
personal experiences.

508
00:20:31.987 --> 00:20:33.967
It is our therapy
in a lot of ways.

509
00:20:34.067 --> 00:20:37.047
and anyone is free
to sit at the table.

510
00:20:37.147 --> 00:20:39.328
We have our support staff.
our writers' assistants.

511
00:20:39.428 --> 00:20:41.448
assistance to EPs. we'll
have them in a room.

512
00:20:41.548 --> 00:20:43.528
'cause. and I can't
emphasize this enough.

513
00:20:43.628 --> 00:20:45.748
best idea wins.

514
00:20:47.549 --> 00:20:50.209
We did an episode where
the South Crenshaw players

515
00:20:50.309 --> 00:20:54.749
and the opposing team take
a stand in solidarity.

516
00:20:57.750 --> 00:20:59.086
It was one of those
moments where you're like.

517
00:20:59.110 --> 00:21:00.970
this isn't a TV show.
like this is a moment.

518
00:21:01.070 --> 00:21:05.531
Like for a moment I forgot
that it was a show.

519
00:21:05.631 --> 00:21:08.771
It was so eloquently done.

520
00:21:08.871 --> 00:21:13.052
To this day. like. that moment
still has an impact on me.

521
00:21:13.152 --> 00:21:15.092
It spoke about things
that were very current.

522
00:21:15.192 --> 00:21:17.172
I think you need
that in society.

523
00:21:17.272 --> 00:21:20.173
You need to hold the mirror
up as much as you can.

524
00:21:20.273 --> 00:21:23.093
These past couple of months
have been really hard.

525
00:21:23.193 --> 00:21:25.009
So because it's hard. you
don't want to do it no more?

526
00:21:25.033 --> 00:21:25.733
I didn't say that.

527
00:21:25.833 --> 00:21:27.974
It's a show that gives hope.

528
00:21:28.074 --> 00:21:31.174
Was very grounded in reality
in regards to the challenges

529
00:21:31.274 --> 00:21:34.494
you may face. but despite
of. you still can overcome.

530
00:21:34.594 --> 00:21:36.451
I know you're going to find a
way back out on that field.

531
00:21:36.475 --> 00:21:38.135
You always do.

532
00:21:38.235 --> 00:21:40.295
My girlfriend is
pregnant. coach.

533
00:21:40.395 --> 00:21:41.095
You'll be ready.

534
00:21:41.195 --> 00:21:42.655
How do you know?

535
00:21:42.755 --> 00:21:44.251
Because you're the most prepared
player I've ever coached.

536
00:21:44.275 --> 00:21:45.776
The power of coaches.

537
00:21:45.876 --> 00:21:48.616
I unfortunately just lost my
high school football coach.

538
00:21:48.716 --> 00:21:50.616
He's yet another
person that I was

539
00:21:50.716 --> 00:21:52.416
able to kind of
draw from in terms

540
00:21:52.516 --> 00:21:54.897
of building Billy Baker's arc.

541
00:21:54.997 --> 00:21:58.397
Look. you tell Layla. she
officially has my approval.

542
00:21:59.837 --> 00:22:01.898
OMG. How did you know?

543
00:22:01.998 --> 00:22:02.738
I'm your father.

544
00:22:02.838 --> 00:22:04.018
I love you. Dad.

545
00:22:04.118 --> 00:22:04.818
Bring it in.

546
00:22:04.918 --> 00:22:05.738
Love you. too.

547
00:22:05.838 --> 00:22:07.138
My love for my dad
and the impact

548
00:22:07.238 --> 00:22:08.778
that he kind of
had on my life has

549
00:22:08.878 --> 00:22:10.699
been incorporated in this show.

550
00:22:10.799 --> 00:22:12.739
You asked me what the
secret to coaching was.

551
00:22:12.839 --> 00:22:13.939
It's simple. man.

552
00:22:14.039 --> 00:22:16.299
I just try to act like a
father to the players.

553
00:22:16.399 --> 00:22:18.100
You were all my kids.

554
00:22:18.200 --> 00:22:19.420
I'm gonna be honest.

555
00:22:19.520 --> 00:22:21.260
You were one of my favorites.

556
00:22:21.360 --> 00:22:24.260
♪

557
00:22:24.360 --> 00:22:26.181
Have you not gotten
your messages?

558
00:22:26.281 --> 00:22:27.541
My dad's bus crashed.

559
00:22:27.641 --> 00:22:29.021
What? The news is saying they

560
00:22:29.121 --> 00:22:30.121
think everyone's okay.

561
00:22:30.201 --> 00:22:32.601
When we lost Billy... brutal.

562
00:22:33.481 --> 00:22:35.142
Brutal.

563
00:22:35.242 --> 00:22:38.262
I think I cried for.
like. five episodes.

564
00:22:38.362 --> 00:22:39.942
Where's Jabari?

565
00:22:40.042 --> 00:22:40.902
Billy. don't.

566
00:22:41.002 --> 00:22:42.022
I have to.

567
00:22:42.122 --> 00:22:44.763
Tell my family that I love them.

568
00:22:46.043 --> 00:22:47.663
[screams]

569
00:22:47.763 --> 00:22:48.503
He's gone.

570
00:22:48.603 --> 00:22:50.603
[sobbing]

571
00:22:51.003 --> 00:22:53.004
My dad is gone.

572
00:22:57.044 --> 00:23:00.505
I was fortunate to receive
a phone call from Taye

573
00:23:00.605 --> 00:23:02.745
before we started that season.

574
00:23:02.845 --> 00:23:04.665
Taye really took
me under his wing

575
00:23:04.765 --> 00:23:08.306
and tried to just show me all
the things of this crazy world.

576
00:23:08.406 --> 00:23:09.786
this crazy business.

577
00:23:09.886 --> 00:23:11.422
Getting the call from him
was. I think. more sad

578
00:23:11.446 --> 00:23:13.186
than Billy's death for me.

579
00:23:13.286 --> 00:23:14.986
(phone ringing)

580
00:23:15.086 --> 00:23:18.187
I just wanted to tell
you some things.

581
00:23:18.287 --> 00:23:21.667
Being your coach had become one
of the best parts of my life.

582
00:23:21.767 --> 00:23:25.508
And I know I'm not your pops.
but I do consider you my son.

583
00:23:25.608 --> 00:23:27.828
You are my All-American.

584
00:23:27.928 --> 00:23:29.268
It was very tough.

585
00:23:29.368 --> 00:23:32.749
Taye is an amazing human
being and an amazing actor.

586
00:23:32.849 --> 00:23:34.189
I'm really close
to these people.

587
00:23:34.289 --> 00:23:38.789
This was an amazing and very
important time of life.

588
00:23:38.889 --> 00:23:41.690
And it's nice to be reminded.

589
00:23:43.970 --> 00:23:47.390
The scenes where Spencer's
struggling with Billy's death.

590
00:23:47.490 --> 00:23:49.311
it's spread across
multiple episodes.

591
00:23:49.411 --> 00:23:52.071
You're in this very
uncomfortable place

592
00:23:52.171 --> 00:23:53.231
for a while.

593
00:23:53.331 --> 00:23:55.151
I directed an episode
within that. too.

594
00:23:55.251 --> 00:23:58.952
so I got to be very present
for Sam's part of the grieving

595
00:23:59.052 --> 00:24:00.632
when she was playing Olivia.

596
00:24:00.732 --> 00:24:02.732
Talk to him.

597
00:24:03.572 --> 00:24:05.873
In here.

598
00:24:05.973 --> 00:24:08.873
Samantha and I are
super. super close.

599
00:24:08.973 --> 00:24:11.993
I've watched her grow
up for eight years.

600
00:24:12.093 --> 00:24:14.074
That's as close to
having a daughter

601
00:24:14.174 --> 00:24:15.954
as I'm gonna experience.

602
00:24:16.054 --> 00:24:19.034
You've been handling
everything so well. and I'm...

603
00:24:19.134 --> 00:24:22.274
I have not been handling
my grief well at all.

604
00:24:22.374 --> 00:24:26.675
Taye and I had spent six
years together every day.

605
00:24:26.775 --> 00:24:30.195
So when Billy died.
I was losing my

606
00:24:30.295 --> 00:24:34.956
partner on the show. so
my heart was broken.

607
00:24:35.056 --> 00:24:38.316
I'm so sorry that you didn't
have more time in it.

608
00:24:38.416 --> 00:24:39.957
[sniffles]

609
00:24:40.057 --> 00:24:43.877
Grieving is not linear. and
it felt like I was grieving.

610
00:24:43.977 --> 00:24:46.357
I decline Coach Baker's call.

611
00:24:46.457 --> 00:24:50.118
My hero. the man
who saved my life.

612
00:24:50.218 --> 00:24:53.198
I had a scene with Daniel
where he screamed at me.

613
00:24:53.298 --> 00:24:55.234
I really don't need you on
my bumper right now. man.

614
00:24:55.258 --> 00:24:56.698
And he punched a
hole in the cabinet.

615
00:24:56.739 --> 00:24:58.479
Leave me alone!

616
00:24:58.579 --> 00:25:00.999
That one for me was kind
of like. all right.

617
00:25:01.099 --> 00:25:03.119
I really feel that.
like this isn't fake.

618
00:25:03.219 --> 00:25:05.280
Everybody's journey in
grief is different.

619
00:25:05.380 --> 00:25:06.860
We kept saying. you
don't get over it.

620
00:25:06.940 --> 00:25:08.120
you learn to live with it.

621
00:25:08.220 --> 00:25:09.760
That was the motto.

622
00:25:09.860 --> 00:25:11.340
We're not gonna make
them get over it.

623
00:25:11.380 --> 00:25:13.481
we're gonna create
sounds and music

624
00:25:13.581 --> 00:25:15.241
that shows how they're
gonna live with it.

625
00:25:15.341 --> 00:25:19.321
You know. I thought I had to
like run away and heal alone.

626
00:25:19.421 --> 00:25:21.042
Thank you guys for
proving me wrong.

627
00:25:21.142 --> 00:25:22.442
I love y'all.

628
00:25:22.542 --> 00:25:23.722
We love you too.

629
00:25:23.822 --> 00:25:25.342
If you don't figure
out how to whisper.

630
00:25:25.382 --> 00:25:27.318
I can tell you someone who's
not going to love you.

631
00:25:27.342 --> 00:25:28.002
[GIGGLING]

632
00:25:28.102 --> 00:25:28.923
I'm sorry.

633
00:25:29.023 --> 00:25:30.363
[WHOOSH]

634
00:25:30.463 --> 00:25:31.999
Over the last year.
I think I've finally

635
00:25:32.023 --> 00:25:34.363
gotten to a place where
I can think about dad

636
00:25:34.463 --> 00:25:35.519
and not feel my gut plunge.

637
00:25:35.543 --> 00:25:37.204
The growth and
continued metamorphosis

638
00:25:37.304 --> 00:25:39.924
of our other characters
were able to happen.

639
00:25:40.024 --> 00:25:42.644
inspired by all the things
that he had taught them.

640
00:25:42.744 --> 00:25:46.325
Raise a hand if. like me.
you are shocked but happy

641
00:25:46.425 --> 00:25:49.205
that these two finally
got their act together

642
00:25:49.305 --> 00:25:50.685
after all these years.

643
00:25:50.785 --> 00:25:52.005
(laughing)

644
00:25:52.105 --> 00:25:55.046
My heart and soul always
made it back to you.

645
00:25:55.146 --> 00:25:59.006
You may now kiss
your damn bride.

646
00:25:59.106 --> 00:26:01.106
(clapping)

647
00:26:03.467 --> 00:26:05.407
The Spencer and Olivia wedding.

648
00:26:05.507 --> 00:26:08.927
to me that felt like the end
because we really didn't know

649
00:26:09.027 --> 00:26:11.088
and we were all together
and so I did a lot of

650
00:26:11.188 --> 00:26:12.648
grieving in that moment.

651
00:26:12.748 --> 00:26:13.848
I thought it was done.

652
00:26:13.948 --> 00:26:15.488
I watched season
six and I was like.

653
00:26:15.588 --> 00:26:18.168
Oh man. I'm gonna
miss this show.

654
00:26:18.268 --> 00:26:21.049
So when the audition came in.
I was shocked and excited.

655
00:26:21.149 --> 00:26:23.069
I had auditioned for
this show since the pilot.

656
00:26:23.149 --> 00:26:25.529
I think it was eight
or so auditions.

657
00:26:25.629 --> 00:26:27.850
Finding out that I was
gonna be a part of it.

658
00:26:27.950 --> 00:26:29.406
I was excited. I wasn't
even really nervous.

659
00:26:29.430 --> 00:26:31.090
I was just ready to go.

660
00:26:31.190 --> 00:26:33.190
I couldn't wait to meet
everyone and get on set.

661
00:26:38.231 --> 00:26:42.091
One of the defining moments
for me personally as an actor

662
00:26:42.191 --> 00:26:44.892
is being able to transition
to something new.

663
00:26:44.992 --> 00:26:48.052
I wasn't entirely sure I
wanted to be a director

664
00:26:48.152 --> 00:26:50.132
until I asked to try it.

665
00:26:50.232 --> 00:26:53.653
I'm so glad I took the leap
because I was among friends

666
00:26:53.753 --> 00:26:56.173
and I was among people
that wanted to see me win.

667
00:26:56.273 --> 00:26:58.933
I could take risks and it
was always met with love.

668
00:26:59.033 --> 00:27:02.254
It forced me to evolve in ways
that I wasn't prepared for.

669
00:27:02.354 --> 00:27:04.494
which is the best way to evolve.

670
00:27:04.594 --> 00:27:07.254
Just when I thought this show
couldn't give me any more.

671
00:27:07.354 --> 00:27:09.355
it gave me some more.

672
00:27:12.115 --> 00:27:16.856
Girl. when I tell you I love
football. I love football.

673
00:27:16.956 --> 00:27:18.336
Blue 32. say go.

674
00:27:18.436 --> 00:27:19.136
I'm fresh.

675
00:27:19.236 --> 00:27:21.016
I'm the new guy in town.

676
00:27:21.116 --> 00:27:23.856
I didn't know how
big of a role I had.

677
00:27:23.956 --> 00:27:25.777
I think I found out
during the table read.

678
00:27:25.877 --> 00:27:29.537
I'm like. OK. yeah.
I'm in this. OK.

679
00:27:29.637 --> 00:27:32.737
I didn't know I was going to be
taking on a lead role like this.

680
00:27:32.837 --> 00:27:34.338
We got royalty around here.

681
00:27:34.438 --> 00:27:35.218
Coaches. son.

682
00:27:35.318 --> 00:27:36.938
That explains the power trip.

683
00:27:37.038 --> 00:27:38.738
It was tossed around
by some people like.

684
00:27:38.838 --> 00:27:40.858
oh. you're the new
Spencer or whatever.

685
00:27:40.958 --> 00:27:42.379
And I'm like. oh.
wait. hold on now.

686
00:27:42.479 --> 00:27:43.939
I can't be the Spencer.

687
00:27:44.039 --> 00:27:45.779
I can't do what Daniel did.

688
00:27:45.879 --> 00:27:48.739
But it was cool to find
out that me and Antonio

689
00:27:48.839 --> 00:27:51.460
are kind of making up
for Spencer's role

690
00:27:51.560 --> 00:27:52.860
as the new hopeful dreamer.

691
00:27:52.960 --> 00:27:53.780
[LAUGHTER]

692
00:27:53.880 --> 00:27:54.880
Oh. my bad.

693
00:27:54.960 --> 00:27:56.016
Watch where the hell
you're going. dog.

694
00:27:56.040 --> 00:27:56.580
Hey. relax.

695
00:27:56.680 --> 00:27:57.940
I said my bad.

696
00:27:58.040 --> 00:28:00.021
I thought I'd come in.
do a couple episodes.

697
00:28:00.121 --> 00:28:01.737
and everybody would move
on with their lives.

698
00:28:01.761 --> 00:28:03.181
Your dad is some big deal crip.

699
00:28:03.281 --> 00:28:04.861
You think that makes
him untouchable.

700
00:28:04.961 --> 00:28:06.297
I didn't think that I'd
be still sitting here

701
00:28:06.321 --> 00:28:07.982
20. 30 episodes later.

702
00:28:08.082 --> 00:28:10.502
I've just been really grateful
to play a character like this

703
00:28:10.602 --> 00:28:13.902
because he represents a lot
of kids in a lot of places.

704
00:28:14.002 --> 00:28:15.423
similar to the places I grew up.

705
00:28:15.523 --> 00:28:16.899
Clearly. a cast like you need
to be taught some respect.

706
00:28:16.923 --> 00:28:18.183
About who?

707
00:28:18.283 --> 00:28:20.363
A brother that's apparently
too stupid to graduate?

708
00:28:21.203 --> 00:28:22.983
What's up?

709
00:28:23.083 --> 00:28:26.264
It's been really cool to
have old cast come back

710
00:28:26.364 --> 00:28:27.900
and sort of tie the
two worlds together.

711
00:28:27.924 --> 00:28:30.024
Spencer James.

712
00:28:30.124 --> 00:28:32.385
I can't believe I'm actually
meeting you right now.

713
00:28:32.485 --> 00:28:33.985
I just hoped everybody
would be nice.

714
00:28:34.085 --> 00:28:35.905
You know. often times
you come into a show

715
00:28:36.005 --> 00:28:38.265
and it's like been on
for six. seven years

716
00:28:38.365 --> 00:28:40.466
and cast is burnt out.
crew doesn't want

717
00:28:40.566 --> 00:28:41.666
to be there anymore.

718
00:28:41.766 --> 00:28:43.366
No one cares about the
story or the plot.

719
00:28:43.446 --> 00:28:45.822
It was beautiful to find that
none of those things were true.

720
00:28:45.846 --> 00:28:48.507
KJ came in like.
"I'm from Oakland."

721
00:28:48.607 --> 00:28:50.343
Guess I just got the Bay
written all over me.

722
00:28:50.367 --> 00:28:53.027
No. but your hat does.

723
00:28:53.127 --> 00:28:54.427
Oh. yeah.

724
00:28:54.527 --> 00:28:55.863
You see the bright colors.
the bright patterns.

725
00:28:55.887 --> 00:28:56.427
They're loud.

726
00:28:56.527 --> 00:28:57.868
They're in your face.

727
00:28:57.968 --> 00:28:59.548
He walks around with
his head held high.

728
00:28:59.648 --> 00:29:01.708
He's very sure of himself.

729
00:29:01.808 --> 00:29:02.904
Must be nice knowing everything.

730
00:29:02.928 --> 00:29:04.748
He's adapting to this
new environment.

731
00:29:04.848 --> 00:29:06.709
new friends. and this
new football team.

732
00:29:06.809 --> 00:29:07.949
I'm from New York.

733
00:29:08.049 --> 00:29:09.309
I moved out here for the show.

734
00:29:09.409 --> 00:29:11.149
This is my first time
ever living on my own.

735
00:29:11.249 --> 00:29:13.590
I made this big
move. just like KJ.

736
00:29:13.690 --> 00:29:15.470
So we're similar in that way.

737
00:29:15.570 --> 00:29:19.030
And if I'm not 100% on
something. I give myself grace.

738
00:29:19.130 --> 00:29:20.390
We're not perfect.

739
00:29:20.490 --> 00:29:22.570
We're all human. and KJ is
a perfect example of that.

740
00:29:22.611 --> 00:29:24.831
I owe you a big apology.

741
00:29:24.931 --> 00:29:28.231
I insulted you and made
all my teammates hate me.

742
00:29:28.331 --> 00:29:30.872
Even though people hurt
us and we hurt people.

743
00:29:30.972 --> 00:29:32.752
that's not where the story ends.

744
00:29:32.852 --> 00:29:34.472
You look like you
could use a friend.

745
00:29:34.572 --> 00:29:36.912
Amina. Amina Sims.

746
00:29:37.012 --> 00:29:38.993
I think people
underestimate what it's like

747
00:29:39.093 --> 00:29:40.393
to have somebody believe in you.

748
00:29:40.493 --> 00:29:42.093
How do you know so
much about football?

749
00:29:42.133 --> 00:29:42.773
I used to play a little.

750
00:29:42.853 --> 00:29:43.673
Yeah. why'd you stop?

751
00:29:43.773 --> 00:29:44.993
I don't know. I just did.

752
00:29:45.093 --> 00:29:47.354
He's not a bad
person. he's just a kid

753
00:29:47.454 --> 00:29:49.954
with a rough past who's
made some mistakes.

754
00:29:50.054 --> 00:29:51.954
Does that remind you of anyone?

755
00:29:52.054 --> 00:29:54.554
Khalil. you have something
very special in you.

756
00:29:54.654 --> 00:29:58.275
What would you say if I wanted
you to come play for me?

757
00:29:58.375 --> 00:30:00.615
That scene was special because
it was like the first time

758
00:30:00.695 --> 00:30:02.295
someone saw Khalil and
believed in Khalil

759
00:30:02.375 --> 00:30:04.956
and wanted him to do better
and saw more for him than what

760
00:30:05.056 --> 00:30:07.396
his circumstances may allow.

761
00:30:07.496 --> 00:30:09.556
Yeah. Yeah. coach. I'll

762
00:30:09.656 --> 00:30:11.116
come play for you.

763
00:30:11.216 --> 00:30:13.557
It reminds me of a lot of people
over the course of my life

764
00:30:13.657 --> 00:30:15.477
that saw something
in me and. you know.

765
00:30:15.577 --> 00:30:17.577
want to help me do something.

766
00:30:19.417 --> 00:30:22.158
We have an opportunity here
to build something great.

767
00:30:22.258 --> 00:30:24.838
KJ and Cassius have a best
friend. brotherly kind of bond.

768
00:30:24.938 --> 00:30:26.598
even though they're
father and son.

769
00:30:26.698 --> 00:30:27.874
All the way into
a bubble screen.

770
00:30:27.898 --> 00:30:28.639
Nice. OK.

771
00:30:28.739 --> 00:30:29.539
But that's how I am with my dad.

772
00:30:29.619 --> 00:30:30.359
We clown on each other.

773
00:30:30.459 --> 00:30:31.279
We joke.

774
00:30:31.379 --> 00:30:32.759
I see what you're doing.

775
00:30:32.859 --> 00:30:35.199
My dad is my best friend.

776
00:30:35.299 --> 00:30:37.200
And I try to bring that into KJ.

777
00:30:37.300 --> 00:30:39.040
I just want to be
certain that I'm putting

778
00:30:39.140 --> 00:30:40.440
you in a position to succeed.

779
00:30:40.540 --> 00:30:41.760
I love that about Cassius.

780
00:30:41.860 --> 00:30:44.521
His ability to learn
from his mistakes

781
00:30:44.621 --> 00:30:47.121
and do what's best for
the people that he loves.

782
00:30:47.221 --> 00:30:50.241
I wanna be more like
Cassius in that respect.

783
00:30:50.341 --> 00:30:52.281
Some of his actions
are questionable.

784
00:30:52.381 --> 00:30:54.482
Are we related to the Bakers?

785
00:30:54.582 --> 00:30:55.838
How long have you
known about this?

786
00:30:55.862 --> 00:30:56.862
All my life.

787
00:30:56.942 --> 00:30:59.682
When he finally
fought for his family.

788
00:30:59.782 --> 00:31:02.443
that's when he really started
to become his own man.

789
00:31:02.543 --> 00:31:04.203
My son is destined
for great things.

790
00:31:04.303 --> 00:31:08.083
but his legacy. that's his own.

791
00:31:08.183 --> 00:31:10.284
Khalil's often misunderstood.

792
00:31:10.384 --> 00:31:13.084
He is very undefinable
in so many ways.

793
00:31:13.184 --> 00:31:15.324
Zero. that's the number I want.

794
00:31:15.424 --> 00:31:16.444
It's all yours.

795
00:31:16.544 --> 00:31:17.885
Nowhere to go but up from here.

796
00:31:17.985 --> 00:31:19.125
I pitched that.

797
00:31:19.225 --> 00:31:20.521
That was the second or
third pitch I've ever made

798
00:31:20.545 --> 00:31:22.205
that actually hit the page.

799
00:31:22.305 --> 00:31:25.285
He chose number zero because
zero is the one character.

800
00:31:25.385 --> 00:31:26.806
numerically. that is undefined.

801
00:31:26.906 --> 00:31:28.806
It's a number. but is
it really a number?

802
00:31:28.906 --> 00:31:30.326
It's time to bounce.

803
00:31:30.426 --> 00:31:32.686
Khalil is in the middle
of taking a test.

804
00:31:32.786 --> 00:31:34.607
What you trying to say?

805
00:31:34.707 --> 00:31:36.287
I can't take my
son out of school?

806
00:31:36.387 --> 00:31:39.367
I get a lot of DMs about how
Preach stepped up to the plate

807
00:31:39.467 --> 00:31:40.887
to watch out for Khalil.

808
00:31:40.987 --> 00:31:46.408
I know where you
really from. Teach.

809
00:31:46.508 --> 00:31:48.808
You should know my whole
get-down. partner.

810
00:31:48.908 --> 00:31:51.329
He kind of steps back into
his old ways to let him know.

811
00:31:51.429 --> 00:31:54.889
"Hey. listen. Street Preach
hasn't gone too far.

812
00:31:54.989 --> 00:31:57.249
He's still there if you
want to push that button."

813
00:31:57.349 --> 00:32:00.210
Take it easy. Teach.

814
00:32:00.310 --> 00:32:01.890
Don't call the hall monitor on
me.

815
00:32:01.990 --> 00:32:03.890
When he decides not to
support his father.

816
00:32:03.990 --> 00:32:05.810
he becomes a man. in my opinion.

817
00:32:05.910 --> 00:32:07.490
I can't go with you. Pop.

818
00:32:07.590 --> 00:32:10.091
It's just more important
than some game.

819
00:32:10.191 --> 00:32:11.251
Now. come on. let's go.

820
00:32:11.351 --> 00:32:12.527
Just 'cause it's
your responsibility

821
00:32:12.551 --> 00:32:13.551
don't make it mine.

822
00:32:13.631 --> 00:32:14.927
You feel like. because
you love someone.

823
00:32:14.951 --> 00:32:16.848
you have to be loyal to
them. but you also have to

824
00:32:16.872 --> 00:32:18.132
be loyal to yourself.

825
00:32:18.232 --> 00:32:21.132
It's all about evolution.
and it's all about growth.

826
00:32:21.232 --> 00:32:23.852
Amina was standing
up for the people

827
00:32:23.952 --> 00:32:25.289
who couldn't stand
up for themselves.

828
00:32:25.313 --> 00:32:27.173
which is something that
her mother taught her.

829
00:32:27.273 --> 00:32:32.534
We are worthy. we are powerful.
and we are everything.

830
00:32:32.634 --> 00:32:35.854
Delivering the speech
was very nerve-wracking.

831
00:32:35.954 --> 00:32:39.974
I. Alexis. felt all
of her real emotions.

832
00:32:40.074 --> 00:32:42.575
I was really proud to help
her take that stance.

833
00:32:42.675 --> 00:32:45.135
She's 16. Preach.

834
00:32:45.235 --> 00:32:48.595
On the cusp of adulthood and
all that comes with that.

835
00:32:50.876 --> 00:32:53.056
Keep balling and
making us proud.

836
00:32:53.156 --> 00:32:56.216
Thank you.

837
00:32:56.316 --> 00:32:58.217
I made my choice.

838
00:32:58.317 --> 00:33:00.757
I want Dinsburg.

839
00:33:03.477 --> 00:33:05.077
We're down to the final
play of the game.

840
00:33:05.157 --> 00:33:06.214
and they're going
to need a miracle.

841
00:33:06.238 --> 00:33:07.258
Boom! 32!

842
00:33:07.358 --> 00:33:10.098
We know KJ wants to win.

843
00:33:10.198 --> 00:33:11.778
When you see him
throw that ball.

844
00:33:11.878 --> 00:33:13.778
it's a relief because
it's the final play.

845
00:33:13.878 --> 00:33:16.079
I'm releasing the ball. like
whatever happens. happens.

846
00:33:18.279 --> 00:33:21.319
But we also feel that pressure
of it at the same time.

847
00:33:24.160 --> 00:33:27.620
When we got the chance
to do a season eight.

848
00:33:27.720 --> 00:33:31.141
it was really about completing
the journey for these kids.

849
00:33:31.241 --> 00:33:34.961
That everything they've
been through was worth it.

850
00:33:46.162 --> 00:33:49.023
I've been a crying mess
for the last three weeks.

851
00:33:49.123 --> 00:33:52.903
I literally delayed
writing the final scene

852
00:33:53.003 --> 00:33:57.344
because if I wrote that scene. I
was gonna write end of series.

853
00:33:57.444 --> 00:34:00.824
I just couldn't write
those final three words.

854
00:34:00.924 --> 00:34:03.865
It was 3:30 in the
morning. and so I finally

855
00:34:03.965 --> 00:34:05.945
wrote the final scene.

856
00:34:06.045 --> 00:34:08.705
And I was crying. and my
husband was looking at me.

857
00:34:08.805 --> 00:34:11.025
and he's like. "Honey.
just hit send."

858
00:34:11.125 --> 00:34:13.106
And I was just
like. "Oh. my gosh.

859
00:34:13.206 --> 00:34:14.206
We're really doing this.

860
00:34:14.286 --> 00:34:16.286
Like. we're really
ending the series."

861
00:34:20.006 --> 00:34:21.907
And then I hit send and
slammed closed my laptop

862
00:34:22.007 --> 00:34:24.827
like it was gonna
implode or something.

863
00:34:24.927 --> 00:34:27.067
All American's family.
it's football.

864
00:34:27.167 --> 00:34:28.467
and it's the friend vortex.

865
00:34:28.567 --> 00:34:30.588
So I really wanted
this final chapter

866
00:34:30.688 --> 00:34:33.788
to climax in a way where
all of those things

867
00:34:33.888 --> 00:34:36.428
reach the best version
of themselves.

868
00:34:36.528 --> 00:34:38.505
There's a lot of turns this
year that I didn't see coming

869
00:34:38.529 --> 00:34:40.549
when I read these scripts.

870
00:34:40.649 --> 00:34:42.225
Some of these characters
are gonna find themselves

871
00:34:42.249 --> 00:34:44.949
in positions that they're
not gonna see coming.

872
00:34:45.049 --> 00:34:47.230
This season challenges
Khalil in every way.

873
00:34:47.330 --> 00:34:48.906
A lot of skeletons
from the past come up.

874
00:34:48.930 --> 00:34:50.230
Hi. son.

875
00:34:50.330 --> 00:34:52.186
He really has to make some
choices about who he is.

876
00:34:52.210 --> 00:34:53.590
who he wants to become.

877
00:34:53.690 --> 00:34:56.151
It's been you. me. and
Dylan against the world

878
00:34:56.251 --> 00:34:57.391
since day one.

879
00:34:57.491 --> 00:34:59.191
This ain't no different.

880
00:34:59.291 --> 00:35:02.032
Today's either gonna be one
of the best days in my career

881
00:35:02.132 --> 00:35:04.272
or one of the biggest
mistakes I'll ever make.

882
00:35:04.372 --> 00:35:07.712
This season is about Spencer
becoming a father himself.

883
00:35:07.812 --> 00:35:10.372
That peace is the peace I
wanted for him this whole time.

884
00:35:13.573 --> 00:35:15.753
He had a severe
superhero complex.

885
00:35:15.853 --> 00:35:17.433
One of several things
that we shared.

886
00:35:17.533 --> 00:35:20.114
My favorite storyline. Spencer
was learning to put that down.

887
00:35:20.214 --> 00:35:21.914
and it helped me put
that down a little bit

888
00:35:22.014 --> 00:35:24.014
in my own personal life. too.

889
00:35:25.854 --> 00:35:28.955
Season eight for Coop's all
about stepping into her power.

890
00:35:29.055 --> 00:35:30.431
You and me are going
to rule the world.

891
00:35:30.455 --> 00:35:31.715
Damn right we are.

892
00:35:31.815 --> 00:35:32.555
There's more law.

893
00:35:32.655 --> 00:35:34.755
There's more of a suit and tie.

894
00:35:34.855 --> 00:35:37.836
There's a more
professional aesthetic.

895
00:35:37.936 --> 00:35:39.436
This season is
challenging for Jordan

896
00:35:39.536 --> 00:35:41.996
because he's met with an
incredible opportunity.

897
00:35:42.096 --> 00:35:44.037
At the same time.
this opportunity

898
00:35:44.137 --> 00:35:46.177
may be the downfall for others.

899
00:35:49.457 --> 00:35:52.958
If season seven for Cassius
was all about him trying

900
00:35:53.058 --> 00:35:55.278
to do right by his
father. season eight

901
00:35:55.378 --> 00:35:57.838
is more about doing
right by his son.

902
00:35:57.938 --> 00:35:59.318
I am proud of you. son.

903
00:35:59.418 --> 00:36:03.479
The KJ that we all know is very
confident. borderline arrogant

904
00:36:03.579 --> 00:36:06.159
sometimes. This
season. we see a crazy

905
00:36:06.259 --> 00:36:08.399
amount of pressure for KJ.

906
00:36:08.499 --> 00:36:12.120
He's learning how to persevere
through different obstacles

907
00:36:12.220 --> 00:36:14.440
that he's never
had to deal with.

908
00:36:14.540 --> 00:36:17.961
Amina is trying to
stand for where

909
00:36:18.061 --> 00:36:19.921
her moral compass is pointing.

910
00:36:20.021 --> 00:36:23.401
I did the right thing.
and I would do it again.

911
00:36:23.501 --> 00:36:24.241
Hey. wait.

912
00:36:24.341 --> 00:36:25.562
Wait. wait. wait. wait.

913
00:36:25.662 --> 00:36:27.602
But instead. everyone
else's opinions

914
00:36:27.702 --> 00:36:31.762
on the choices she's making
in her life are very harsh.

915
00:36:31.862 --> 00:36:33.443
KJ. it's bad.

916
00:36:33.543 --> 00:36:35.439
And I don't know what I'm
going to do in the minute

917
00:36:35.463 --> 00:36:38.323
but I gotta find Tom.

918
00:36:38.423 --> 00:36:39.323
Come. Come here.

919
00:36:39.423 --> 00:36:41.423
Come. come. come.

920
00:36:42.864 --> 00:36:44.724
She's back.

921
00:36:44.824 --> 00:36:46.904
I'm a little scared that I
function a little too well

922
00:36:46.984 --> 00:36:48.324
on the road without him.

923
00:36:48.424 --> 00:36:50.005
What if I'm turning into my dad?

924
00:36:50.105 --> 00:36:52.081
I think the really beautiful
thing about her journey

925
00:36:52.105 --> 00:36:54.165
is that where her mental
health is concerned.

926
00:36:54.265 --> 00:36:55.965
it wasn't sort of
like a storyline

927
00:36:56.065 --> 00:36:57.885
that we did and wrapped
up in one episode.

928
00:36:57.985 --> 00:37:00.246
Every season we see
how that evolves.

929
00:37:00.346 --> 00:37:02.326
This season. she's
reverting back

930
00:37:02.426 --> 00:37:04.166
to some of her old patterns.

931
00:37:04.266 --> 00:37:07.127
And it's very much about her
learning to be vulnerable again

932
00:37:07.227 --> 00:37:08.887
and lean on the
people closest to her

933
00:37:08.987 --> 00:37:11.007
and not sort of
take everything on

934
00:37:11.107 --> 00:37:14.287
and feel like she has
to do that alone.

935
00:37:14.387 --> 00:37:15.688
Welcome home.

936
00:37:15.788 --> 00:37:17.724
As individuals. we get caught
in our own thing of just.

937
00:37:17.748 --> 00:37:18.648
it's about me.

938
00:37:18.748 --> 00:37:20.168
And it's not.

939
00:37:20.268 --> 00:37:22.648
It's about others that may
not have the voice to fight.

940
00:37:22.748 --> 00:37:23.609
You two sit down.

941
00:37:23.709 --> 00:37:24.849
I'm going to handle this.

942
00:37:24.949 --> 00:37:27.209
This season. I think
Preach does a good job

943
00:37:27.309 --> 00:37:28.969
standing up for people.

944
00:37:29.069 --> 00:37:30.089
(screaming)

945
00:37:30.189 --> 00:37:31.285
This year. it's
forcing people to move

946
00:37:31.309 --> 00:37:32.566
a little bit out of
their comfort zone.

947
00:37:32.590 --> 00:37:35.450
Enough. everyone. go to
a corner and cool off.

948
00:37:35.550 --> 00:37:37.170
There's a huge
episode coming up.

949
00:37:37.270 --> 00:37:39.206
At the very start of the
season. I said to the studio.

950
00:37:39.230 --> 00:37:40.367
I was like. I'm just
gonna be honest.

951
00:37:40.391 --> 00:37:41.811
this is the one I'm
gonna fight for.

952
00:37:41.911 --> 00:37:43.527
It's important to me
that we tell this story.

953
00:37:43.551 --> 00:37:45.811
I watched friends. I
watched kids I know

954
00:37:45.911 --> 00:37:47.011
have to deal with this.

955
00:37:47.111 --> 00:37:48.972
I think it's important
that we show our kids

956
00:37:49.072 --> 00:37:50.448
dealing with it. but I'm
not gonna say what it is.

957
00:37:50.472 --> 00:37:53.332
I'm gonna let people guess.

958
00:37:53.432 --> 00:37:58.413
The fans. they're getting ready
to graduate with all of us.

959
00:37:58.513 --> 00:38:01.213
Everyone kept saying.
"It's the last scene in

960
00:38:01.313 --> 00:38:02.533
the Crenshaw hallway."

961
00:38:02.633 --> 00:38:05.054
That was when I think
I finally realized

962
00:38:05.154 --> 00:38:07.894
it was coming to an end.

963
00:38:07.994 --> 00:38:09.534
There was like a lot
of amazing people

964
00:38:09.634 --> 00:38:12.614
who have walked those halls.

965
00:38:12.714 --> 00:38:14.735
It completely changed
the course of my life

966
00:38:14.835 --> 00:38:16.615
in really beautiful ways.

967
00:38:16.715 --> 00:38:19.775
There are many. many moments
that was very accurate

968
00:38:19.875 --> 00:38:21.496
to what was happening
in our lives.

969
00:38:21.596 --> 00:38:23.416
People got married.
people got divorced.

970
00:38:23.516 --> 00:38:27.536
people had babies.
people lost parents.

971
00:38:27.636 --> 00:38:30.497
Hey. Layla. thank
you for the dance.

972
00:38:30.597 --> 00:38:32.737
This week. we did the
final read-through.

973
00:38:32.837 --> 00:38:34.373
It was like the longest
read-through we've ever had

974
00:38:34.397 --> 00:38:36.017
because we kept having
to stop and start

975
00:38:36.117 --> 00:38:37.937
'cause people were just
crying and tearing up.

976
00:38:38.037 --> 00:38:40.258
We were wrapping
sets every other day.

977
00:38:40.358 --> 00:38:43.178
Which means the wrapping
of a writer and a director.

978
00:38:43.278 --> 00:38:46.499
It really. like. moved my heart.
'cause these people have been

979
00:38:46.599 --> 00:38:48.599
here since the beginning.

980
00:38:50.279 --> 00:38:51.279
[ Cheers and applause ]

981
00:38:51.359 --> 00:38:54.660
This place was a
very special family.

982
00:38:54.760 --> 00:38:57.460
You can't say that about
everything you work on.

983
00:38:57.560 --> 00:39:00.140
I have a family.
and I have friends.

984
00:39:00.240 --> 00:39:02.620
I was one of the youngest
people at the time I came in.

985
00:39:02.720 --> 00:39:04.581
I felt like a
little caterpillar.

986
00:39:04.681 --> 00:39:06.661
Now I feel like I can fly.

987
00:39:06.761 --> 00:39:08.781
[ Cheers and applause ]

988
00:39:08.881 --> 00:39:11.181
I will never let go of Spencer.

989
00:39:11.281 --> 00:39:13.338
This is the most significant
character I've ever played.

990
00:39:13.362 --> 00:39:15.302
I'll go on and I'll wear
different costumes.

991
00:39:15.402 --> 00:39:17.542
but he'll be with
me all the time.

992
00:39:17.642 --> 00:39:19.823
I don't think our fans are
ready for this to end.

993
00:39:19.923 --> 00:39:20.983
I don't.

994
00:39:21.083 --> 00:39:22.863
I think they will
love what's coming.

995
00:39:22.963 --> 00:39:25.383
Hands down. they will not
be ready for the ending.

996
00:39:25.483 --> 00:39:26.383
It's game time.

997
00:39:26.483 --> 00:39:28.484
Game time.

998
00:39:29.684 --> 00:39:31.984
We finished strong.

999
00:39:32.084 --> 00:39:37.725
(crowd cheering)

1000
00:39:44.005 --> 00:39:48.946
Oh my gosh. to our
fans. I'm a writer. so

